Satcon Wins Contract for 10-Megawatt U.S. Solar Power Plant

-- B y   K a t i e   L i n s e l l
-- 
2011-08-16T10:49:22Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-16/satcon-wins-contract-for-10-megawatt-u-s-solar-power-plant.html
Satcon Technology Corp ., a solar-
panel manufacturer, won a contract for the 10-megawatt  New
Jersey  Oak Solar power plant.  Satcon will deliver 10 of its 1-megawatt “prism platform
solutions” to the facility, constructed by units of Houston,
Texas-based Quanta Services Inc., it said in a  statement . The
project is owned by Chicago-based Lincoln Renewable Energy LLC.  When completed this year, the plant at Fairfield Township,
New Jersey, will be the largest non-utility owned solar
development east of the Mississippi river, the company said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Katie Linsell in London at 
 Klinsell@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
